H2Adapter

Class SetAdapter<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • H2Adapter.SetAdapter<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements in this set
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Set<E>

    public class SetAdapter<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Set<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>
    Simple Generic Set interface adapter for J2ME Class Hashtable.

    Since the adaptee is an Hashtable this set does not allow null elements.

    See also: SetAdapter.SetAdapterIterator

    Author:
    Manfè Alessandro 1201538

        public boolean addAll(java.util.Collection<? extends E> c)
        Adds all of the elements in the specified collection to this set if they're not already present. If the specified collection is also a set, the addAll operation effectively modifies this set so that its value is the union of the two sets. The behavior of this operation is undefined if the specified collection is modified while the operation is in progress.

Returns true if the specified object is also a set, the two sets have the same size, and every member of the specified set is contained in this set (or equivalently, every member of this set is contained in the specified set). This definition ensures that the equals method works properly across different implementations of the set interface.

      • toArray

        public java.lang.Object[] toArray()
        Returns an array containing all of the elements in this set.

        Array is a shallow copy and it's not backed to the set. Structural changes to the set do not affect the array, therefore it is to be considered an invalid reference.

        The returned array will be "safe" in that no references to it are maintained by this set. (In other words, this method must allocate a new array even if this set is backed by an array). The caller is thus free to modify the returned array.

        Specified by:
        toArray in interface java.util.Collection<E>
        Specified by:
        toArray in interface java.util.Set<E>
        Returns:
        an array containing all the elements in this set
